Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.94,0:00:05.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The body of Saeki Yuri-san, the woman who \Nwent missing with the Tears of Borgia,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:08.19,Hiromichi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Umeki Hiromichi (45)\NKanoya Construction Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.99,0:00:12.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}a jewel scheduled to be used as part of a live \NTV drama broadcast forty years ago, was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.04,0:00:16.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Saeki Yuri-san's granddaughter Sumire-san
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:17.09,Sumire,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Saeki Sumire (20)\NSaeki Yuri's Granddaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.73,0:00:21.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}hired the Mori Detective Agency \Nto clear Yuri-san's name,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.64,0:00:22.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.89,0:00:26.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mizusawa-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.53,0:00:30.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say something \Nabout the whatever of Borgia?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.90,0:00:31.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.34,0:00:37.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Something's burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.28,0:00:41.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A fire? Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.64,0:00:42.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.47,0:00:44.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hot, hot, hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.13,0:00:47.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hot, hot, hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:48.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.45,0:00:50.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.58,0:00:53.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right now at this moment, \Nlight pierces the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:56.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Overcome all limits with \Nyour cool reasoning skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:57.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A skeleton emerges across time and space!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.88,0:01:00.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The case catches fire, putting \Nthe old man in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.01,0:01:01.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.56,0:01:03.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.28,0:01:05.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:53.02,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}The Cursed Tears of Borgia \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.75,0:02:51.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Cursed Tears of Borgia, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.37,0:02:57.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:00.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet. We're in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.05,0:03:03.95,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you're doing okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:06.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's just a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:09.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.56,0:03:13.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, I'm \Nsorry for all the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.35,0:03:14.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:18.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't save Mizusawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.47,0:03:23.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't he the one who found \NSumire-san's grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.30,0:03:26.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He was my drinking buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.31,0:03:29.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He said he had something \Nto discuss with me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.07,0:03:33.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. If only I'd gotten there sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.66,0:03:35.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,About that, Mori-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.32,0:03:43.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The autopsy revealed that he \Nhardly inhaled any smoke at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.48,0:03:47.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So by the time the fire \Nstarted, he was already...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.27,0:03:48.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:54.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.40,0:03:56.46,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:03:57.88,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.63,0:03:59.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:03.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Forensics just called.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:09.30,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They examined the victim's phone \Nthat Mori-san saved from the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.30,0:04:12.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't a single image saved on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.89,0:04:13.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.44,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't just the images.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:20.87,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from Mori-san's, they didn't find \Na single fingerprint on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.87,0:04:23.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.93,0:04:29.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone erased all the images on the \Nphone and wiped their prints off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:31.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:37.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and it's probably the same person
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.03,0:04:38.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,who murdered Mizusawa and started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.03,0:04:39.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:42.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What about the erased data?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:45.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We're having forensics restore it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.10,0:04:46.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:50.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, you were supposed to \Nmeet the victim at six, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:51.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.62,0:04:55.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember anything \Nfrom when the fire started?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.61,0:05:00.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the situation, the fire was \Nstarted about thirty minutes earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't have been more than an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:07.84,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Mizusawa was murdered before that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.84,0:05:10.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,between 5 and 5:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:12.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about his associates' alibis?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.26,0:05:17.58,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Nonogaki Real Estate, the site \Nof the fire, was closed today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.01,0:05:19.98,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't been able to \Nconfirm the whereabouts
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.98,0:05:23.82,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,of President Nonogaki \Nor any of his employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.82,0:05:25.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.19,0:05:26.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Also,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.76,0:05:33.57,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,the victim's friend and client Kanoya \NConstruction President Umeki Hiromichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.21,0:05:35.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that name before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.55,0:05:36.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.85,0:05:41.74,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Umeki-san was with the victim when \Nthey discovered the body at the dam.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.31,0:05:44.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:47.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And? What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.38,0:05:52.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He saw the news about the \Nfire on a TV at a bar
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.04,0:05:54.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and came to talk to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:59.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to him, he'd been drinking \Nwith several friends since around five.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:03.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So only Umeki has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.76,0:06:07.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister. Don't you want to \Nsee photos of the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:08.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.72,0:06:13.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You might be able to figure \Nsomething out if you saw it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.99,0:06:16.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. What do you think, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.95,0:06:19.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Bring them immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:21.37,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:25.90,Text,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,From: Kanoya Tatsuma \NSubj: No Subject \NI found the kine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:28.90,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Kinescope?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:33.13,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the powdered roasted \Nsoy beans you put on mochi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.13,0:06:35.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Before video became widespread,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:35.90,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, silly me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.90,0:06:37.60,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I was thinking of kinako.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.93,0:06:39.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they used to convert important images \Nto film in order to preserve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.30,0:06:46.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoya-san kept a kine, not kinako,\Nof the final scene of "I Killed Them."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:53.35,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,That's a valuable record, but it's \Nnot like it will solve the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:58.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I already know who killed Mizusawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:06:58.98,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.64,0:07:03.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're going for the other case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.68,0:07:06.73,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,This brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.05,0:07:10.24,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,"I Killed Them," or \N"Killed 'Em" for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:13.87,Tatsuma,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kanoya Tatsuma (72)\NKanoya Construction Advisor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.32,0:07:13.00,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,You remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:18.62,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Indeed I do. I think I was \Nin sixth grade at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:20.12,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,My, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:23.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister. Was the window \Nopen in the final scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:26.02,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,No, we closed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:31.42,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't want to distract from Nagisa-chan \Nin the important final scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.42,0:07:35.51,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be ruined if the wind blew the curtains.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.27,0:07:39.64,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, that \Nline was incredibly intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.88,0:07:43.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. No, but maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:46.37,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandson is rather strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.37,0:07:47.90,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:53.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.23,0:07:57.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.50,0:08:03.75,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,We've gathered the others, \Nbut where are we headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.24,0:08:06.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The dam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:08.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want to \Ncheck at the filming location.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.81,0:08:18.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,According to Kanoya-san, \Nit should be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:21.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.68,0:08:26.88,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.88,0:08:28.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.08,0:08:28.52,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.24,0:08:31.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Beika City is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.02,0:08:33.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:36.63,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Knew what? H-Hey, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.63,0:08:38.03,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.35,0:08:47.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.77,0:08:49.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.37,0:08:53.05,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I have someplace to be after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.65,0:08:56.20,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Probably a gambling hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.10,0:09:00.64,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you're being threatened by \Nsome suspicious people recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.59,0:09:05.39,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:08.06,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,He's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.75,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,This way, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.75,0:09:14.77,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.77,0:09:16.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.52,0:09:19.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Inspector. You're here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.44,0:09:22.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.43,0:09:25.83,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who asked us to \Ncome here to solve the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.09,0:09:27.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:31.11,DCMain,TAKAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:32.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hot, hot, hot! T-Today has been too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.11,0:09:32.94,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:33.63,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That was quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.62,0:09:38.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.53,0:09:40.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.52,0:09:46.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, I asked you to come \Nhere to discuss the two cases
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:51.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,surrounding the jewel known \Nas the Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.18,0:09:53.11,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.60,0:09:57.28,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt I have anything to \Ndo with that, so I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.63,0:10:02.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, its connection to you will \Neventually emerge, Umeki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.26,0:10:10.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure some of you have heard \Nthat Western history scholar Senju
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.20,0:10:17.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,said the Tears of Borgia didn't actually \Nexist and that the jewel was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:18.38,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.62,0:10:21.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, though the jewel itself was fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.89,0:10:27.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Saeki Yuri-san who was transporting \Nit was indeed found dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.58,0:10:32.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, 40 years is quite the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.08,0:10:36.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,People thought it impossible \Nto determine the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:40.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But a new incident occurred in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.50,0:10:44.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Its victim was one of the \Nmen who discovered Yuri-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:47.33,Sho,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,410)}Mizusawa Sho (25)\NNonogaki Real Estate Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.24,0:10:46.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Mizusawa Sho-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.93,0:10:51.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but he was \Nkilled not by the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.45,0:10:55.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but by someone who strangled him to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.84,0:10:59.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The investigation briefly \Nproceeded under the assumption
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:02.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,that the culprit was someone who had \Nno alibi for when the fire started,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:07.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but the crime scene suggested the \Nexistence of another culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:09.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, the photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.28,0:11:11.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:12.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.88,0:11:16.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The platter that should be \Non the shelf is on the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.78,0:11:18.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and the bottles are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:20.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you suppose that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.99,0:11:28.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's because that's a picture \Nof a timed ignition device
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:31.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,made from the materials on hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:42.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This device the culprit made to get away
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.30,0:11:47.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,with his crime instead limited \Nwho the culprit could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.50,0:11:53.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, whoever has an alibi for \Nthe time the fire started is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:55.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right, Umeki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.04,0:11:59.69,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I have no reason to kill Mizusawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.88,0:12:03.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Takagi, the photos from \Nthe phone at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:05.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.15,0:12:10.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,These two photos were restored \Nfrom the phone's deleted data.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.21,0:12:13.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They show the glovebox of \Nthe car Yuri-san was riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.28,0:12:17.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the time these photos were taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:22.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The first was taken at 9:41,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:25.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,while the second was taken at 9:51.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.90,0:12:29.80,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,The glovebox that was closed \Nin the first photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.23,0:12:31.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,...is open in the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.24,0:12:36.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Chiba, what time was the body reported?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.67,0:12:38.48,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,9:45 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.95,0:12:43.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Mizusawa-kun \Nphotographed the car at 9:41.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.81,0:12:49.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he switched with you and \Nreported the body at 9:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.33,0:12:55.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He then returned to the car \Nand photographed it at 9:51.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:57.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Umeki-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.70,0:13:00.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,while Mizusawa-kun was away \Nfrom the car for ten minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.58,0:13:05.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you're the only one who \Ncould've opened the glovebox.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.51,0:13:09.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When Mizusawa-kun noticed \Nthe open glovebox later,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:13.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he suspected you took something from the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:17.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He tried to discuss it with \Nme, but you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:19.02,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:23.85,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying the Tears of Borgia \Nwas inside that glovebox?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.78,0:13:28.45,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I know about that ancient history?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.09,0:13:31.34,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm disappointed, Hiromichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.34,0:13:36.71,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you about the Tears of Borgia \Ncountless times when you were a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:39.77,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:42.09,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,For this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:44.46,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,For this damn fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:47.88,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:48.47,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.28,0:13:54.39,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's fake, my grandmother \Nrisked her life for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:57.06,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:13:59.46,DCMain,UMEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.19,0:14:14.41,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,So who stabbed my grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.60,0:14:20.75,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to take over for Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.75,0:14:22.29,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.56,0:14:26.84,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. After all, it happened forty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:30.05,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,And it's more speculation than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:33.77,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm better suited for \Nthis than Detective Mori.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:37.93,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoya-san, could you prepare the kine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.36,0:14:39.75,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.19,0:14:50.84,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoya-san preserved the final scene
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:55.37,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,of the forty-year-old drama \N"I Killed Them" on 16 mm film.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.37,0:15:00.37,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,The maid played by Nagisa-chan calls \Nover her boyfriend the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.89,0:15:07.66,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,This is the scene suggested by Yuri-san \Nin which she begins peeling apples, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.66,0:15:09.34,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.38,0:15:17.10,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,"Red Hood has arrived"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:31.79,DCItalic,BUTLER,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.87,0:15:34.14,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Masao-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:40.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Didn't you say only Nagisa-san \Nwent to the filming location?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.97,0:15:36.06,DCItalic,MASAO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Were you waiting long?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.06,0:15:38.97,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No, but I was scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:42.96,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Since this card was here, I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.04,0:15:41.76,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.76,0:15:46.23,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But look. The man playing the \Nbutler is there with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:49.12,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,The butler's at the studio set.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:49.42,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Masao-san, do you not \Nneed to walk with a cane?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.12,0:15:49.94,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.74,0:15:53.97,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,We're switching cameras at set times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:53.71,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Masao-san, are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.16,0:16:00.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But the maid is in the scene with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:03.37,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,That's a stand-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.83,0:16:05.61,DCItalic,RED HOOD,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Give me the Tears of Borgia \Nyou're wearing on your finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.37,0:16:06.31,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,We had a similar-looking actress
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:11.07,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,wear the same costume and \Nstand in for Nagisa-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.58,0:16:07.66,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.60,0:16:10.58,DCItalic,RED HOOD,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.54,0:16:13.32,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,This shot was done on location.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:17.23,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Then we switched to the studio here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.00,0:16:15.71,DCItalic,RED HOOD,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Damn it! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.71,0:16:17.23,DCItalic,RED HOOD,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Where did you go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.23,0:16:18.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.66,0:16:20.66,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you pause it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.47,0:16:26.97,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of the scenes are \Nunrelated to the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:28.67,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,so we'll leave them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.16,0:16:33.30,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to present my theory to you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.70,0:16:37.30,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Sumire-san, I'd especially \Nlike you to hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.34,0:16:39.56,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.34,0:16:42.97,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,While the drama was being \Nfilmed at the studio,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.97,0:16:46.56,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-san waited on location \Nfor her scene to start
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:50.48,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,and for Yuri-san to arrive \Nwith the Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.93,0:16:54.61,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,However, she never arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.87,0:16:57.12,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-san must've panicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.19,0:17:01.06,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Nagisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.29,0:17:04.31,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,We have three more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.92,0:17:12.30,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,We need to film the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.65,0:17:15.30,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,You're late, Yuri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.25,0:17:17.78,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,She won't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.33,0:17:23.30,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan! I'm glad you made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.08,0:17:26.14,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly, the Tears of Borgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.28,0:17:32.65,DCMain,AGSA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-san had been convinced by Professor \NSenju not to embarrass the family with a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.26,0:17:35.28,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,They were both desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.64,0:17:40.16,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-san had no time to explain, and \NNagisa-san had a 40 degree fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.86,0:18:12.44,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-san tried to get as far away \Nfrom the location as she could
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.72,0:18:15.44,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,so Nagisa-san wouldn't be blamed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:21.18,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,and so the fake Tears of Borgia \Nwouldn't appear in the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:34.55,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,At the studio, the stand-in \Nmaid stabbed Red Hood to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.94,0:18:38.01,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,All that remained was \NNagisa-san's final shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.71,0:18:43.11,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-chan, the real jewel \Nwon't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.11,0:18:46.56,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but you'll have \Nto wear the fake ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.51,0:18:49.28,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:58.15,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:04.58,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.92,0:19:07.10,DCItalic,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.01,0:19:15.09,TheEnd,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(290,1)}The End
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.46,0:19:26.47,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I imagine \Nhappened behind the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.84,0:19:30.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that your story explains
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.78,0:19:35.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the fallen car and the fruit knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:40.15,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,And Nagisa-san's current condition, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.33,0:19:43.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bad that it's only speculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.66,0:19:45.28,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:50.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, didn't you say you had them \Nclose the window for the final scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:54.93,DCMain,AKNOYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was necessary for the performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.93,0:19:58.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then if the window was open,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.27,0:20:00.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't that prove Yuri-san came?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:07.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be conclusive, but it \Nwould be circumstantial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.06,0:20:11.68,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,But since the curtains were closed, we \Ndon't know if the window was opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.02,0:20:17.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I saw something shining when \Nyou showed us this film
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.39,0:20:19.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,on the editor this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:26.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just before the words "The \NEnd" appear onscreen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:30.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,when Nagisa-san disappears from the shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:31.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:37.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see something shining \Nthrough the lace curtains?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.86,0:20:39.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.89,0:20:41.85,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,How embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.85,0:20:44.68,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't noticed in forty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.85,0:20:49.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That proves the professor's story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.04,0:20:50.09,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.09,0:20:53.08,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can report the results to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.40,0:20:56.71,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.71,0:20:57.94,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be a star?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.94,0:20:58.69,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.91,0:21:02.78,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,It was cloudy that day. There \Nwasn't a single star in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.78,0:21:05.13,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then was it plane lights?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.68,0:21:06.82,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,A plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.70,0:21:09.83,DCMain,KANOYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.14,0:21:11.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.04,0:21:13.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This light was probably
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:20.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the now demolished Beika \NCity aerial lighthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.33,0:22:48.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Several days later,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.64,0:22:54.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we learned Asahina Nagisa-san \Nkept calling Yuri-san's name,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.22,0:22:58.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so we went to Grand Light with \NSumire-san where Nagisa-san lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.71,0:22:59.85,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.64,0:23:08.99,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-chan, you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.68,0:23:14.24,DCMain,SUMIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I've been fine this \Nwhole time, Nagisa-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.79,0:23:16.34,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.34,0:23:20.19,DCMain,NAGISA,0000,0000,0000,,I had such a long and terrible dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.21,0:23:32.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nagisa-san's heart, which had been tormented
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.52,0:23:36.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,by the ring's curse for forty long years,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.33,0:23:42.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,was released by the kindness of one \Ngrandmother and her granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.86,0:23:49.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.62,0:23:53.20,DCMain,SHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,It's only once a day, so enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.45,0:23:55.91,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,The dinosaur bones fell apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.68,0:24:00.04,DCMain,KUCHIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it! My brachiosaurus!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.65,0:24:04.54,DCMain,NAITO,0000,0000,0000,,Like you, I wanted everyone to enjoy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.76,0:24:09.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But it was only for a few seconds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Man Crushed by a Dinosaur
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.53,0:24:13.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NMan Crushed by a Dinosaur!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Dinosaur Show
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.88,0:24:32.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint, roar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.83,0:24:34.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A dinosaur show!
